00:08:05.262 --> 00:08:08.261
This is the same thing as one plus one

00:08:08.261 --> 00:08:10.094
minus 3/10,

00:08:11.727 --> 00:08:13.232
and this one right over here

00:08:13.232 --> 00:08:17.110
is the same thing as 10/10,

00:08:17.110 --> 00:08:19.600
and so 10/10 minus 3/10.

00:08:19.600 --> 00:08:22.381
That over there is going to be,

00:08:22.381 --> 00:08:25.277
that is going to be 7/10,

00:08:25.277 --> 00:08:27.558
so it's going to be one and 7/10,

00:08:27.558 --> 00:08:29.142
which is what we got before.

00:08:29.142 --> 00:08:30.877
So the whole point here is to appreciate

00:08:30.877 --> 00:08:34.054
there's multiple strategies
for subtracting decimals,

00:08:34.054 --> 00:08:36.166
some that you can do a little
bit more automatically,

00:08:36.166 --> 00:08:37.425
but it's really good to think about

00:08:37.425 --> 00:08:38.559
what's going on in your head.

00:08:38.559 --> 00:08:41.212
And some strategies are
actually better in your head

00:08:41.212 --> 00:08:42.422
